§§ `Validation Functions`

GIVEN code IS A STRING
GIVETH A BOOLEAN
`is valid ISO 3166-1 alpha-2` MEANS
    LENGTH code EQUALS 2
    AND code EQUALS TOUPPER code

GIVEN code IS A STRING
GIVETH A BOOLEAN
`is valid ISO 3166-1 alpha-3` MEANS
    LENGTH code EQUALS 3
    AND code EQUALS TOUPPER code

GIVEN code IS A STRING
GIVETH A BOOLEAN
`is valid ISO 3166-2` MEANS
    LENGTH code AT LEAST 4
    AND SUBSTRING code 0 2 EQUALS TOUPPER (SUBSTRING code 0 2)
    AND SUBSTRING code 2 1 EQUALS "-"


§§ `Country Name Lookup`

GIVEN code IS A STRING
GIVETH AN EITHER STRING STRING
`country name from alpha-2` MEANS
    IF code EQUALS `United States alpha-2` THEN RIGHT "United States"
    ELSE IF code EQUALS `United Kingdom alpha-2` THEN RIGHT "United Kingdom"
    ELSE IF code EQUALS `Canada alpha-2` THEN RIGHT "Canada"
    ELSE IF code EQUALS `Australia alpha-2` THEN RIGHT "Australia"
    ELSE IF code EQUALS `Germany alpha-2` THEN RIGHT "Germany"
    ELSE IF code EQUALS `France alpha-2` THEN RIGHT "France"
    ELSE IF code EQUALS `China alpha-2` THEN RIGHT "China"
    ELSE IF code EQUALS `Japan alpha-2` THEN RIGHT "Japan"
    ELSE IF code EQUALS `Singapore alpha-2` THEN RIGHT "Singapore"
    ELSE IF code EQUALS `India alpha-2` THEN RIGHT "India"
    ELSE IF code EQUALS `Brazil alpha-2` THEN RIGHT "Brazil"
    ELSE IF code EQUALS `Mexico alpha-2` THEN RIGHT "Mexico"
    ELSE IF code EQUALS `Switzerland alpha-2` THEN RIGHT "Switzerland"
    ELSE IF code EQUALS `Netherlands alpha-2` THEN RIGHT "Netherlands"
    ELSE IF code EQUALS `Sweden alpha-2` THEN RIGHT "Sweden"
    ELSE IF code EQUALS `New Zealand alpha-2` THEN RIGHT "New Zealand"
    ELSE IF code EQUALS `South Korea alpha-2` THEN RIGHT "South Korea"
